## Theming (apply to `<html>`)

- `data-color-scheme="dark"` ‚Äî dark mode
- `data-theme="resman|anyonehome|inhabit"` ‚Äî brand
- `data-font="poppins|roboto|lexend"` ‚Äî font family
- `data-font-scale="smaller|larger"` ‚Äî text scale
- `data-density="comfortable"` ‚Äî relaxed spacing

## Do's and Don'ts

DO: `color: var(--uds-color-text-primary)` / DON'T: `color: #171717`
DO: `padding: var(--uds-space-200)` / DON'T: `padding: 16px`
DO: `font-family: var(--uds-font-family)` / DON'T: `font-family: 'Inter'`
DO: `border-radius: var(--uds-border-radius-input)` / DON'T: `border-radius: 8px`

### React specific:
- Use `className` not `class`
- Use `useState` for component state (open/close, selected, checked)
- Use controlled inputs (`value` + `onChange`)
- NEVER use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`
- NEVER load `uds.js` ‚Äî React manages state with hooks

### Vue specific:
- Use `<script setup>` with `ref()` from vue
- Use `v-model` for inputs, `@click` for events, `:attr` for bindings
- NEVER use `v-html`
- NEVER load `uds.js` ‚Äî Vue manages state with refs
